-- Russia Proposes Blacklist for Internet Websites, Kommersant Says
-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 2012-06-08T05:26:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/russia-proposes-blacklist-for-internet-websites-kommersant-says.html
Russian deputies proposed creating a
register of sites containing illicit information that can only
be accessed by service providers and telecom operators,
 Kommersant  reported, without citing anyone.  The register will include “a blacklist” of sites
featuring child pornography and promoting drugs and illegal
substances, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  